snippet: Nevertheless, analysts warned that growing stockpiles could easily force prices down again.
abstract: Global oil prices rise above $60 a barrel after traders bid up on encouraging reports of Europe's economy; experts warn that growing stockpiles, due to excess of up to two million barrels being stored per day, could force prices back down.
lead_paragraph: Nevertheless, analysts warned that growing stockpiles could easily force prices down again.

headline.main: Oil Prices Up 3% on News of Economic Growth in Europe, but Supplies Rise
headline.print_headline: Oil Prices Up 3% on News of Economic Growth in Europe, but Supplies Rise
